Class BaseService

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.ibm.team.repository.common.transport.ITeamRestService, com.ibm.team.repository.common.transport.services.IService

    public abstract class BaseService
extends com.ibm.team.repository.service.TeamRawService
    Entry point for the ExampleService, called by the Jazz class loader.

    This class must be implemented for enabling plugins to run inside Jazz. The implemented interface corresponds to the component in plugin.xml, and this service is therefore the provided service by the interface.

      • performAction

        protected void performAction(String uri,
                             javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                             javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
                      throws IOException
        Calls the requested method and handles errors.

        With the current architecture, it's easier to have dummy public methods and handle them all with this single function. Error handling in jazz is a bit special, and to guarantee that the service is functionally sound, all errors except 501 and IOExceptions should be handled internally. If not handled and logged, a generic 500 exception is returned with little help for debugging.

        Parameters:
        uri - Relative URI to which the request was sent
        request - ServletRequest object that contains all request information
        response - A wrapped IO Handler for responses
        Throws:
        IOException - Only exception thrown back to Jazz, corresponding with the contract from the inherited method.
